## 1. Purpose
This Statement of Applicability records which security control domains and requirements are applicable to [COMPANY]'s ISMS, the justification for inclusion or exclusion, the current implementation status, and the policy or evidence that satisfies each control. It is the single point of traceability between [COMPANY]'s risk decisions, the HITRUST CSF, and the operating policy set, and it demonstrates to assessors that control selection is deliberate and complete.

## 2. Scope
The SoA covers every applicable control across the systems, data, locations, and people defined in `isms-scope-statement.md.template`. Control applicability is determined by the HITRUST CSF scoping factors (organizational, system, regulatory) selected in MyCSF, the risk assessment (`../risk/risk-management-methodology.md.template`), and applicable legal/regulatory obligations (`../compliance/legal-and-regulatory-compliance.md.template`).

## 3. Policy
1. A SoA **shall** be maintained covering all in-scope control domains, with no applicable control omitted.
2. Each control **shall** record an applicability decision (Yes/No), and every exclusion **shall** carry a documented justification.
3. Each applicable control **shall** record an implementation status and reference the policy/procedure and evidence that satisfies it.
4. Applicable controls that are not yet fully implemented **shall** have a corresponding entry in the POA&M register (`corrective-action-poam.md.template`).
5. The SoA **shall** be the authoritative mirror of the MyCSF object and **shall** be reconciled to it before each assessment and at each management review.
6. The SoA **shall** be reviewed and re-approved at least annually and upon material scope or risk change.

## 4. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [CEO / Board] | Approves the SoA and the residual risk it represents. |
| [Security Officer / CISO] | Owns the SoA; maintains MyCSF; assigns control owners. |
| Control Owners | Maintain implementation status and evidence for assigned controls. |
| [Internal Audit] | Tests that recorded statuses match reality. |

See `roles-and-responsibilities.md.template` for full role definitions.

## 5. Applicability Status Legend
| Status | Meaning |
|---|---|
| Implemented | Control is operating and evidenced |
| Partially Implemented | Control is in place but with gaps; POA&M required |
| Planned | Approved and scheduled; POA&M required |
| Not Implemented | Applicable but not yet started; POA&M required |
| Not Applicable | Excluded; justification required |

