## 7. Exclusions Summary
[COMPANY] **shall** maintain a clear summary of all controls marked Not Applicable with their justifications, so that exclusions can be reviewed in aggregate during assessment. Exclusions premised on subservice organizations (e.g., [AWS], [Snowflake]) **shall** reference the supporting assurance (SOC 2 report, attestations) tracked under vendor risk management.

## 8. Exceptions
Where an applicable control cannot currently be met, the gap is documented as a POA&M item and, where it represents accepted risk, as an exception per `exceptions-and-waivers.md.template` — time-bound and approved by the [Security Officer] and [CEO].

## 9. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
The SoA is validated through internal audit (`internal-audit-program.md.template`), continuous control monitoring, and management review. Discrepancies between recorded and actual control status are findings tracked to closure in the POA&M register. Control owners are accountable for keeping their entries accurate.

